    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Timothy",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "Counsel is given to teach true doctrine only\u2014Christ came to save repentant sinners.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the commandment of God our Saviour, and Lord Jesus Christ, which is our hope;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Unto Timothy, my own son in the faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God our Father and Jesus Christ our Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 16:1 (1\u20134); 1\u00a0Cor. 4:17.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0lawful, true.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As I besought thee to abide still at Ephesus, when I went into Macedonia, that thou mightest charge some that they teach no other doctrine,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:3 (3\u20135); 3\u00a0Ne. 11:40.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 1:8 (6\u20138).",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Neither give heed to fables and endless genealogies, which minister questions, rather than godly edifying which is in faith: so do.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Titus 1:14; 2\u00a0Pet. 1:16.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0offer, present.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:4.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Edification.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Now the end of the commandment is charity out of a pure heart, and of a good conscience, and of faith unfeigned:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 5:14.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Tim. 2:22.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "From which some having swerved have turned aside unto vain jangling;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0missed the mark.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0vain, idle, fruitless discussion.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Desiring to be teachers of the law; understanding neither what they say, nor whereof they affirm.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0strongly assert.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But we know that the law is good, if a man use it lawfully;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing this, that the law is not made for a righteous man, but for the lawless and disobedient, for the ungodly and for sinners, for unholy and profane, for murderers of fathers and murderers of mothers, for manslayers,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Law of Moses.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Godliness.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 3:19.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For whoremongers, for them that defile themselves with mankind, for menstealers, for liars, for perjured persons, and if there be any other thing that is contrary to sound doctrine;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Whore.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0homosexuals.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Homosexual Behavior.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0kidnappers.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Tim. 4:3.",
                        "start": 172,
                        "end": 180
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "According to the glorious gospel of the blessed God, which was committed to my trust.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trustworthiness.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who hath enabled me, for that he counted me faithful, putting me into the ministry;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Philip. 4:13.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who was before a blasphemer, and a persecutor, and injurious: but I obtained mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 26:9.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 8:3; 22:4.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0violent.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 7:25.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 9:39 (39\u201341). TG\u00a0Ignorance.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the grace of our Lord was exceeding abundant with faith and love which is in Christ Jesus.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This is a faithful saying, and worthy of all acceptation, that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners; of whom I am chief.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 3:1.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 9:13 (12\u201313). TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Atonement through.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 5:32; John 9:39 (39\u201341).",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1507
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Howbeit for this cause I obtained mercy, that in me first Jesus Christ might shew forth all longsuffering, for a pattern to them which should hereafter believe on him to life everlasting.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Mercy of.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 105
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Example.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now unto the King eternal, immortal, invisible, the only wise God, be honour and glory for ever and ever. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:15 (15\u201316).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Eternal Nature of; Immortality.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "This charge I commit unto thee, son Timothy, according to the prophecies which went before on thee, that thou by them mightest war a good warfare;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 4:14 (14\u201316); 2\u00a0Tim. 1:6.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Holding faith, and a good conscience; which some having put away concerning faith have made shipwreck:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:24; D&C 6:13.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals; Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Of whom is Hymen\u00e6us and Alexander; whom I have delivered unto Satan, that they may learn not to blaspheme.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Tim. 2:17.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 19:33 (33\u201334).",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 5:5; D&C 78:12; 104:10 (9\u201310); 132:26.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}